    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Containers, commonly made of aluminum or plastic, designed to both facilitate the even application of paint onto a commercial paintroller and hold unused paint during the painting process. Such containers comprise a centralized paint well or reservoir into which the paint may be added, as well as roller ramps to engage the roller, one or more side walls fitted with end wipers to remove excess paint, a drainage spout, and four outboard legs to support the device while in use.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
